The paper discusses the performance analysis of $\ell_1$-optimization in solving under-determined systems of linear equations, which is a fundamental problem in compressed sensing. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also provides alternative performance analysis and improves on the best currently known proportionality constants, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Additionally, the paper involves numerical optimization and solving linear systems, which are relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper discusses sparsity and compressed sensing, which are relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
